\sum _{n=2}^{\infty } \frac{(-1)^n}{\sqrt{n}+(-1)^n}
\sum\limits_{k=1}^\infty \left(a_{2k}+a_{2k+1}\right)=\sum\limits_{k=1}^\infty \left(\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{2k}+1}-\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{2k+1}-1}\right)=
\sum\limits_{k=1}^\infty \left(\dfrac{\sqrt{2k+1}-\sqrt{2k}}{(\sqrt{2k}+1)(\sqrt{2k+1}-1)}-\dfrac{2}{(\sqrt{2k}+1)(\sqrt{2k+1}-1)}\right)
\sim \frac{1}{const\cdot k^{3/2}}
\sim \frac{1}{const\cdot k}
